{# FAQ #}
<section class="py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-10">Common Questions About Visa Sponsorship</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4" id="faq-list">

      <div class="card overflow-hidden faq-item">
        <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pr-4">How do I know if a company sponsors visas?</span>
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 shrink-0 faq-icon transition-transform duration-200"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <div class="prose-custom">
            <p>Check the company's careers page for mentions of visa sponsorship or relocation support. You can also use our checker above to search verified companies. In the UK, you can check the official <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/register-of-licensed-sponsors-workers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Home Office sponsor register</a>.</p>
            <p>Additionally, browse our <a href="/visa-sponsored-jobs/">visa-sponsored job listings</a> to find positions that explicitly offer sponsorship.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card overflow-hidden faq-item">
        <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pr-4">What is the UK sponsor register?</span>
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 shrink-0 faq-icon transition-transform duration-200"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <div class="prose-custom">
            <p>The UK sponsor register is a public list maintained by the Home Office showing all licensed sponsors authorized to issue Certificates of Sponsorship for Skilled Worker visas. Companies must be on this list to legally sponsor work visas in the UK.</p>
            <p>You can view the register on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/register-of-licensed-sponsors-workers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UK government website</a>. For more information, see our <a href="/resources/country-guides/uk/">UK country guide</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card overflow-hidden faq-item">
        <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pr-4">What is the EU Blue Card?</span>
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 shrink-0 faq-icon transition-transform duration-200"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <div class="prose-custom">
            <p>The EU Blue Card is a work and residence permit for highly qualified non-EU nationals. It requires a recognized university degree and a binding job offer with a minimum salary threshold. Germany is the most popular destination for EU Blue Card holders.</p>
            <p>Learn more in our <a href="/resources/country-guides/germany/">Germany country guide</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card overflow-hidden faq-item">
        <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pr-4">Do companies pay for visa sponsorship?</span>
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 shrink-0 faq-icon transition-transform duration-200"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <div class="prose-custom">
            <p>In most cases, the sponsoring employer covers the visa application fees and legal costs. Many also provide full relocation packages including flights, temporary housing, and moving expenses. However, this varies by company and country.</p>
            <p>Check our <a href="/resources/relocation-tips/">relocation tips</a> for what to expect and how to negotiate a better package.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card overflow-hidden faq-item">
        <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pr-4">Can I switch companies while on a sponsored visa?</span>
          <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 shrink-0 faq-icon transition-transform duration-200"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <div class="prose-custom">
            <p>Yes, but the process depends on the country and visa type. In most cases, your new employer must also be an authorized sponsor and file a new sponsorship application. You typically cannot work for the new employer until the transfer is approved.</p>
            <p>For country-specific details, explore our <a href="/resources/country-guides/">country guides</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

